description:
&lt;p&gt;The Performance Analysis Team is an analytical service supporting NHS England and NHS Improvement national and regional teams by providing information and analysis to inform policy and operational decisions. Our service spans the whole analytical pipeline, from data development and data collection, through to reporting and bespoke analysis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Example projects include: Modelling to inform Spending Review discussions with the Department of Health and Her Majesty’s Treasury&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-depth analysis to shape the Long-Term Plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collecting and assuring plans to ensure that local health systems can deliver the care their patients need within the resources they have available&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitoring in-year delivery and working with local health systems to improve performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Performance and Analysis team operate from Leeds, London and Regional offices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note although these roles are primarily Leeds based, there may be an option to work from one of our London offices in one or more of the roles.  If you are interested in these roles and are selected for an interview, please discuss your location preferences at interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Performance and Analysis Team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: england.performanceanalysisteam@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please include the role you are enquiring about in your email.&lt;/p&gt;
